47:20.640 --> 47:20.760
Right.

47:20.760 --> 47:27.320
But Flyxion argues that true, robust alignment cannot be based on identical outputs.

47:28.140 --> 47:32.100
True alignment requires sharing the same admissible geometry.

47:32.640 --> 47:33.520
Ah, right.

47:33.520 --> 47:39.140
Remember our discussion on trajectory equivalence, meaning is the path, not the destination.

47:39.500 --> 47:42.380
If you don't take the path, you don't actually possess the meaning.

47:42.600 --> 47:43.160
Exactly.

47:43.600 --> 47:49.180
If an AI does not share our constraint bounds, if it doesn't have a biological prior forcing

47:49.180 --> 47:54.280
it to manage entropy and avoid vorticity, it cannot be fundamentally aligned with human

47:54.280 --> 47:54.740
reasoning.

47:54.860 --> 47:56.040
It's an alien intelligence.

47:56.540 --> 48:01.920
It does not experience meaning as a stable trajectory through a semantic field.

48:01.920 --> 48:09.460
It is simply an incredibly advanced statistical engine producing strings of words that mimic the

48:09.460 --> 48:14.460
endpoint of our thoughts without ever experiencing the geometry of the concepts.

48:14.620 --> 48:17.820
Endpoint equivalence with massive path divergence.

48:18.300 --> 48:20.840
And that makes the model inherently unpredictable.

48:21.360 --> 48:21.840
How so?

48:21.840 --> 48:27.700
If it has only learned to mimic the results without learning the underlying transformational structure,

48:27.840 --> 48:34.900
the stretches, twists, and projections, then the moment it faces a completely novel situation

48:34.900 --> 48:41.860
outside its training data, its lack of a biological prior will cause it to behave in ways that

48:41.860 --> 48:44.380
are fundamentally alien to human logic.

48:44.380 --> 48:50.760
That is a devastating critique of how the tech industry currently trains these massive language

48:50.760 --> 48:51.140
models.

48:51.280 --> 48:51.920
There really is.

48:51.980 --> 48:57.600
We're training them to teleport to the right answer, rewarding them for skipping the journey

48:57.600 --> 49:04.060
and then acting surprised when they hallucinate or fail to understand basic physical constraints.

49:04.080 --> 49:04.280
Yes.

49:04.680 --> 49:08.720
We are building alien geometries and trying to force them to wear human masks.

49:08.720 --> 49:11.220
It is a profound paradigm shift.

49:11.660 --> 49:15.960
And remarkably, Flyxion doesn't stop at linguistics or AI.

49:16.320 --> 49:16.900
There's more.

49:17.200 --> 49:22.560
In the final major section of the paper, the framework zooms out from individual words

49:22.560 --> 49:26.220
and tasks to look at the macro level of the entire brain.

49:26.420 --> 49:27.300
Okay, zooming out.

49:27.500 --> 49:34.340
It asks, how does this geometric theory explain the overall limits of human intelligence?

49:34.340 --> 49:38.200
And does it touch upon the nature of consciousness itself?

49:39.020 --> 49:41.040
This is the spectral geometry section.

49:41.320 --> 49:46.460
We're moving from the micro level of Nantes' words back to the macroscopic physics of the

49:46.460 --> 49:46.800
mind.

49:47.020 --> 49:47.360
Yes.

49:47.820 --> 49:54.080
To understand how efficiently amplit-wist cascades can propagate across the entire brain,

49:54.280 --> 50:00.160
we have to analyze the global topological shape of the representational manifold.

50:00.400 --> 50:00.660
Okay.

