And this required looking at spectral geometry, specifically the Laplace-Biltromi operator.

50:06.940 --> 50:08.860
The math gets incredibly dense here again.

50:08.960 --> 50:09.780
I need to ground this.

50:10.560 --> 50:14.320
What exactly is a Laplace-Biltromi operator and what does it have to do with my brain?

50:14.640 --> 50:21.700
In physical terms, the Laplace-Biltromi operator describes how things diffuse, vibrate, or propagate

50:21.700 --> 50:24.340
across a curved surface or manifold.

50:24.740 --> 50:26.040
Diffuse or vibrate.

50:26.040 --> 50:32.160
Think about how heat spreads across a sheet of metal, or how sound waves vibrate across

50:32.160 --> 50:33.280
